{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_lima_ver02/data/sn83045433/100493305/1910061801/0256.xml":{"full_text":"WALL STREET NEWS\nfT v\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\"e\u2014\u2014\nNew Low Record in Point of\nSales for the Year.\nShares to 11 4. Pe a\nShares to rb ot pid sg Sno 8 Catlett. \u00a7I0, Yan\nEr \u2014\u2014_\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\nTO-DAY WILL AIS0O BE DULL\nP\u2014\u2014\u2014 v fam ie a ann V. Mihov we. Wash\nRoosevelt Parade Expected to Take\nAttention Away from Financial\nDistrict\u2014Prices Rise on Small Vol\nume of Dealing\u2014Confidence in\nEconomic Future Daily Increased.\nws, demurrer over-| 8 10 Ro bert 5. Williams, $6.\nj returnable June 24. Attommeys, J. B., Rhodes. nstave A,\nruled. Attorneys, Pennebaker (amsi e Eigith stroet northwest, bel seen G and H streets\n1% No. 27756. Cats Jones, Square 4%, part of Jot 7; Alfred A. Walker et\nJames A. Cahill et nx. and David J. Dunnigan\nNew York, June 17.\u2014Disagreeable\n\u2018Weather, a general expectancy that stock\nexchange business to-morrow would be\npractically suspended on account of the\nRoosevelt parade and other similar rea\nsons were suggested to-day as account\ning for the particular dullness of the\nstock market. The lightness of the trad\ning was, however, doubtless due, in great\npart, to the same broad reasons that\nhave beeu operating to compress business\nthroughout the present week, ang the\nmost important fact about to-day\u2019s busi\nness was that the turnover of stocks was\nonly 9.000 shares, new low record in\npoint of volume for the entire year, and\nsince July 3, 1908, when but 72,000 shares\nwere bought and sold,\nGittings Chamberlain\u2014H Ww i\nvs, $10.\n\nNo 241. Turubwrke vs, Koblen; time to file of i\nBe ied Attorney, W. G. Gardine; A\n4 Sol\net al, i\n4\n\n\n\n3\n\nerent\n\n\nAside frqm this the only other notable\nfeature of the market was that prices\nrose slightly and that if anything pro\nfessional sentiment in Wall street ap\npsared to be scmewhat more cheerfully\ninclined. The probable early adjournment\nof Congress and the homecoming of Mr.\n\n\ni\norgan were naturally regarded as fa\nvorable factors. Alsec the market seems\nat the moment to be In a mor\u00e9 or less\noversold condition and presenting no evi\ndences of a resumption of liquidation.\n\n\nHeld Steady at Slight Advance,\nThe greater number of stocks held\nthroughout business hours at prices from\nPa to 1-2 per cent above those of yester\nday and closed at practically the same\nlevel.\nhe tone somewhat, mortgages), well secured cm real estate is\n\nIn all the markets to-day the most\nstriking development was a relatively\nlarge break in the cotton uptions due\nostensibly to a report that the Federal\ngrand jury, which has lately been investi\ngating the so-called cotton pool operating\nfor the rise in cotton, was about to hand\ndown an indictment found against the!\nmembers of the clique.\n\nAs a general proposition it seems to be\ntrue that confidence in the financial and\neconomic future is being daily increased\nby the strongly declining tendency in all\ncommodity prices; by the effect that this\nmust have upon the cost of living, and\nby the increasing bank reserves and nu\nmerous other evidences that business is\ncoming down from a state of inflection to\nsound and stable basis.\n\n\nober 2B\nQuotations fursished by W. B. Hibbs Co., mem\nbers of the New York Stock Exchange Hibbs Build\nig ar ew en\nFeorredtt.restonnat,\nentire 3 Port Wor 13.60 13 820 1 i\nasansess sins py a g111 oo\nNipissing Mines Co......o.. mM... BS a 4 ax\nyy Olio RREEED 1 {oust reve gens 1,000 10.8 03,963,000 li September SHAPE\na ae en RR\nfig b 8\n3\nLin THE\nNEW YORK MONEY.\n1\nwt\nork, June 17.-Money on call at the stock\nto-day opened at 3 per cent, highest 3\nlowest 2%, closing 2% per cent. Most of the day's\nloans were made at 2% per cent.\ngupon, 1\n\nTime money continued easy, with a small demand\nsufficient funds to supply borrowers, Rates,\ndays, 3 per cent; nine