 cent over 1308\nand 16.9 per cent cver 1806. The best de\nvelopment is the turn in foreign trade,\nwhich, during Mav, showed an excess\nof exports of $11,215,820 as compared with\nan excess of $7,262,243 in 1908, and of\n$20,567,750 in 1908. Thus there is a return\nto normal conditions.\u201d\nfi Po-|\nGRAIN AND PROVISIONS.\nQuotations furnished by W. R. Hibs Co,\nof the Chicago Board of Trade, Hibbs\n\ni}\nChicago, June 17.\u2014Wheat opened steady to a\n\u2018shade firmer and ruled strong throughout the ses\nsion, Weather conditions in the Northwest were\n\u2018the controlling factor. Minneapolis reported cash\ndemand good. St. louis wired some cutting of\nwheat in Missouri, The market closed with a good\nundertone,\nLocal receipts eleven cars, with six estimated for\nprices were inchanged.\nLocal cars 283, with 22 estimated for to-morrow,\nOats mled generally firmer, Local professionals\nbought on Be strength in wheat. Commission\nhouses were sellers.\nLocal receipts HT cars, with 9 sstimated for to\nWOTTOW,\nBearish hog news made a lower market for pro\n\nvisions, but the buying of pork late in the day\nadvance, and rallied the rest\nDecember PEE 2%\nrasan\nBEY caninsse aseriznsss 35\nsab diaasate 38\nOATS\nJuly cane snnn EE\nSeptember ...oioiisninss By\nDecember ....cooveenne. Whe\nLARD\nJuly TATRA RIRRERRARN YS seerecil i\nRIBS~\niE inn TIPE 12%\nSeptember ....cocvvee.. JAB\nQEIORNBE wavssvasssssserres 1206\nSeptomber\nJuly\nHigh. Low. Close.\nBE VK HS\nLE] 9% 9%\n2% Ax eu\nBele FN B56\nFe \u00a5e\n4% i 5\nIE BN WI\nBy 35 11-16 3%\n3% 1518 3% He\n128 123% 123%\nBY 12% ns\nne un ns\nWHEAT Ope\n12 12% ne\n2 RO Bs\n20 2&8 1219\nnw 2H ze\n2 Zr 28\ni gs\nDecember. 9\nHe\nBALTIMORE GRAIN MARKET.\nLIVE STOCK MARKET.\nLOCAL GRAIN MARKET.\nDAILY COURT RECORD\nDISTRICT COURTS.\nEgunity Court No. 1,\nJUSTICE ANDERSON.\ninervene; reference to. nditr Attorney, J. C\nnd C. E.\nNo, 2:69, Stotts Park Plock;\na op\nA\nNo, 28815. Butler va. Butler; leave to withdraw\nAppearanc